        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <date>27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. Sept<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 1860</date>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>– I am haunted with a kind of misgiving, which bye &amp; bye I shall be able to express more clearly—that the multiple origin of the dog will furnish an argument for the multiple origin of a Mammal, or of Man. Do try to consider it that way, for I incline to go far with Hooker (&amp; with you?) in believing that whatever is true in domestication is essentially possible in Nature also, &amp; I am not sure that you confine the multiple origin of the dog to Man’s selection.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

